Interface PluginI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPlugin, Node_AccessPointP, Node_RoutingP, Node_TerminalP
    public interface PluginI
extends Serializable
    The interface PluginI defines the basic implementation services of component plug-ins seen as objects.

    Description

    This interface is implemented directly or indirectly by all objects implementing a plug-in. The default

      void setPreferredExecutionServiceURI​(String executorServiceURI)
      set the URI of the executor service used to execute simulations; this method must be called at most once before installing the plug-in on the owner component.
      default void uninstall()
      uninstall the plug-in from its owner component.
